description:
With the March 24 State of Emergency, the President of the Democratic Republic of Congo also imposed a 30-day long ban on all travel to and from capital of Kinshasa in order to allow the confinement of Kinshasa, the source of the pandemic. This includes:

"A ban on all passenger flights in both directions Kinshasa - Provinces, except for aircraft carrying freight, whose crews will be subject to strict controls on departure and arrival;
A ban on all migratory movements, by means of commercial transport, of buses, trucks and other vehicles from the interior to Kinshasa and from Kinshasa to the interior. Barriers must be erected by the government, and crews must submit to strict control of the Coronavirus;
A ban on all river transport of passengers from Kinshasa to the Provinces and vice versa.
Only ships and boats carrying goods with crews and conveyors will be authorized."

